article.headline: Lamar 57, SE Louisiana 52
article.story: HAMMOND, La. -- Anthony Miles scored six of his 16 points in the final minute to lead Lamar past Southeastern Louisiana 57-52 on Wednesday night, snapping the Lions' 13-game home winning streak. Stan Brown added 13 points and 10 rebounds for the Cardinals (11-14, 5-6 Southland Conference), who trailed 50-49 with 1:08 left to play. Miles hit two free throws with 50 seconds to go, giving Lamar a 51-50 lead. Four more free throws from Miles and two from Charlie Harper in the final 23 seconds sealed the win. Southeastern Louisiana (12-11, 6-5) led 27-23 at halftime, but an 11-for-21 shooting effort (52.4 percent) from the Cardinals in the second half was too much to overcome. David Ndoumba scored 15 points and grabbed 11 rebounds for the Lions, who hadn't lost inside the University Center since Jan. 16, 2010. DeShawn Patterson added 10 points for Southeastern Louisiana.
